# Goal Description

The image generation feature is failing on the frontend with the error "Image failed to load." This happens because the backend proxy is currently fetching `https://pollinations.ai/p/[prompt]`, which returns an HTML page instead of the actual image data. The `<img>` tag in the frontend then fails to parse the HTML as an image, triggering the `onError` event.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend Service
I will fix the target URL in the router to hit the raw image endpoint instead of the website renderer.

#### [MODIFY] [image.generate.route.js](file:///c:/Users/KIIT0001/Desktop/Perplexity/Backend/src/routes/image.generate.route.js)
Update the URL definition to use `image.pollinations.ai/prompt/`:
```javascript
let imageUrl = `https://image.pollinations.ai/prompt/${encodedPrompt}?width=${width}&height=${height}&model=${model}&nologo=true`;
```

